<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" ;
	dprr:hasID 9805 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7755> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7755" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. Pl. 44. See MRR 2.324, 559. Delete the filiation, which is unattested, and note that he served under Mark Antony in Macedonia as well as Syria. See Syme, RP 1.31-41.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7755 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6285> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6285" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus (Liv. Per. 127; Vell. 2.78.1; Flor. 2.19.4), probably with imperium. The Parthian invaders of Syria under Labienus drove him out of Syria, captured him in Cilicia, and put him to death (Liv. Per. 127; Flor. 2.19.4, inexact; Iustin. 42.4.7; Dio 48.25; Porphyr., on Hor. Carm. 3.6.9)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6285 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6250> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6250" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus (Liv. Per. 12 7; Vell. 2.7 8. 1) under Antony in Syria, probably with imperium like other governors of the period (cf. Dio 48.25). See 40, Legates." ;
	dprr:hasID 6250 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6185> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6185" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commander (no title preserved), along with Norbanus Flaccus, of the advance forces of Antony and Octavian in Macedonia (App. BC 4.87; Dio 47.35.2). The forces of the Liberators turned their positions at both the Corpilan and the Sapaean passes, and compelled them to retreat behind Philippi (Plut. Brut. 38; App. BC 4.102-104, and 107; Dio 47.35-36; Zonar. 10.19)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6185 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6022> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6022" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Antony and Dolabella carried about mid-June a bill to establish a commission of seven (Cic. Att. 15.19.2; Phil. 5.21; 8.26; 12.23) with L. Antonius as chairman to divide all available public land among veteran soldiers and needy citizens (Cic. Phil. 5.7; Dio 45.9.1; cf. Cic. Att. 15.12.2, and 15.1, and 17.1, and 19.2; 16.3.1; Phil. 5.20; 7.17; 13.37; on Antony and Dolabella, see Phil. 5.33; 11.13; on L. Antonius, Phil. 5.20; 6.13; 7.16-17; 11.13; 12.20; 13.37; on Lento and Nucula, Phil. 2.99; 6.14; 8.26; 11.13; 12.20 and 23; 13.2 and 26 and 37; on C. Antonius, Att. 15.19.2, which is against including him. Saxa and Cafo had received lands in Campania, and Saxa was a skilled surveyor who expected to use his art, Cic. Phil. 8. 9 and 26; 10. 22; 11. 12 and 37; 12.20; and on Saxa also Phil. 2.99; 11.13; 13.2 and 27; 14.10; on both, see Syme, JRS 27 [1937] 127-137; and D.-G. 1.83, note 4). The law was declared invalid on January 4, 43, by decree of the Senate on the ground that it was carried by force (Cic. Phil. 5.7 and 2 1 ; 6.14:; 11. 13)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6022 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5974> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5974" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "One of Caesar's appointees to the office (Cic. Phil. 11.12; 13.27; cf. Dio 43.51.6; see below, Special Commissions, and 43, Legates). Hostilius and Decidius were termed tribunicii when in Antony's camp in 43 (Cic. Phil. 13.27). Against Niccolini (FTP 356) 1 am inclined to date their tribunates in 44." ;
	dprr:hasID 5974 .
